statements.sql: select `product_id`, `status` from `ec_bookings` right join `ec_orders` on `ec_bookings`.`order_id` = `ec_orders`.`id` where `PickingUpDate` <= 1688277600 and `DroppingOffDate` >= 1688277600 and `status` = 'completed'

select count(*) as aggregate from `ec_products` left join
(
SELECT ec_season.cost,
ec_season.base_price,
ec_season.product_id
FROM ec_season
WHERE
ec_season.startDate <= '1688277600' and ec_season.endDate >= '1688277600'
and  ec_season.Duration = (
SELECT MAX(s2.Duration)
FROM ec_season s2
WHERE
s2.startDate <= '1688277600' and s2.endDate >= '1688277600'
and  s2.Duration <=  0  AND
s2.product_id = ec_season.product_id )
)
